programme.desc: 9/17/22: Amed Rosario collects four RBIs and hits a walk-off single in the bottom of the 15th inning to help the Guardians edge the Twins, 7-6, in the second game of a doubleheader.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 9/20/22: On a brisk autumn night, Aaron Judge suddenly is one home run shy of Roger Maris' record and sparks an epic Yankees' comeback against the Pirates. Giancarlo Stanton feels the electric momentum and walks it off with a grand slam in the Bronx.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/7/52: Mickey Mantle's 6th inning home run and Billy Martin's game-saving catch help the New York Yankees win their 4th straight World Series, beating the Brooklyn Dodgers in 7 games.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/14/65: Sandy Koufax finishes a complete-game shutout in Game 7 of the 1965 World Series to bring home a championship. The Dodgers' 2-0 victory was capped in the top of the 4th inning when runs scored on a homer and an RBI single.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/15/70: After allowing three runs in the 1st inning, Mike Cuellar silenced the Reds over the next eight frames to pitch a complete game. The Orioles offense backed his start, scoring nine runs on 15 hits to take Game 5 and win the 1970 World Series.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/22/75: Tony Pérez started the Reds' comeback in Game 7, smashing a two-run home run over the Green Monster and onto Lansdowne Street. Jim Burtan scored Ken Griffey in the top of the 9th to break a 3-3 tie and give the Reds their third World Series win.

programme.title: Great Games
programme.desc: 10/18/77: With one game away from a World Series win, "Mr. October" Reggie Jackson knocks three homers against three different Dodgers pitchers and Mike Torrez pitches a complete game. The Yankees win 8-4 and take home a championship.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coral Islands
programme.desc: The reef systems that gave rise to coral islands support the vast majority of marine species on our planet, but they are under threat. Explore the delicate balance between exploiting and preserving these extraordinary natural wonders.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Bridges
programme.desc: A bridge is a structure that’s designed to transcend, but a great bridge can define the place where it stands. Symbols of human ingenuity, beauty, and grandeur, bridges connect us not only to each other but also to the past.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Drives
programme.desc: A journey by road expands our horizons, allowing us to explore the depth and breadth of whole countries and continents, stopping whenever and wherever we chose.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Volcanic Islands
programme.desc: They've been worshiped and feared over the millennia. But in the wake of drama and destruction, the elements give rise to cultures and nations so beautiful that we've come to know them as the world's greatest volcanic islands.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Iconic Buildings
programme.desc: In construction, only a few buildings can be groundbreaking. Vastly different in shape, size, and function, these diverse buildings prove there is no recipe for greatness, just the fundamental ingredients of vision, bravery, and imagination.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Treks
programme.desc: Every journey made by foot promises a grand adventure. From the highest mountains to the wildest jungle realms, treks venture down the road less travelled, allowing us to connect to nature, history, and culture, one step at a time.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Port Cities
programme.desc: Some of the most stunning cities are port cities - Sydney, Rio, Cape Town - and are also some of the most culturally diverse and vibrant. The great maritime cities of the world bridge countries and continents and unite the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Glaciers
programme.desc: Clinging to the world’s highest mountains and forming ice caps on both poles, glaciers leave an impression on the landscape and on all who bear witness to their splendor.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Marine Animals
programme.desc: From the surprises of colorful reef characters to effervescent penguins, killer sharks, and regal whales, dive into the places where nature reveals itself in some of its most marvelous and bizarre forms.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Deserts
programme.desc: For all their reputation as inhospitable places, deserts are full of incredible plants and animals that have adapted to the climate. They are bursting with geological wonders that inspire and are home to some of the most life in the world.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Timeless Cities & Towns
programme.desc: These cities and towns are special places where the past coexists with the present, creating cultures totally unique to their people and their part of the world and adhering to ancient traditions and while introducing modern innovations.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Nearshore Islands
programme.desc: Some of the world’s greatest islands are so close that they blend in with the mainland. But regardless of their size and origins, they are often the islands we are drawn to the most, each forging their own unique identity.

programme.title: War Story: Across the Rhine: Paras in Germany
programme.desc: In mid-September 1944, the remnants of the battered 1st Canadian Parachute Battalion participated in the largest parachute drop in history, fought a successful battle.
programme.sub-title: Across the Rhine: Paras in Germany

programme.title: War Story: Out of the Clouds: Paras in Normandy
programme.desc: In Normandy, the 1st Canadian Parachute Battalion proved itself to be in the vanguard of the best-trained and toughest units in the Allied forces.
programme.sub-title: Out of the Clouds: Paras in Normandy

programme.title: War Story: The Road to Rome
programme.desc: The Road to Rome examines the incredible experiences of Canadian veterans, the victories and horrors of armoured combat, and the pivotal value, far too often neglected, of the overall Italian Campaign.

programme.title: War Story: Ortona: The War Inside
programme.desc: The War Inside is a personal retelling of one of the fiercest battles of the Italian Campaign from the searing points of view of Canadian infantrymen, a tanker, a stretcher bearer, and a German paratrooper.

programme.title: War Story: Sicily: The First Campaign
programme.desc: The Sicily Campaign began with the largest seaborne invasion in history on 9-10 July 1943. The Allied forces of Britain, Canada, and the United States sought to knock Italy out of the war and attack Germany from the south.

programme.title: War Story: Bomb Girls Remember
programme.desc: During the Second World War, 250,000 Canadian women helped to build the arsenal of democracy. These young women met the challenges of factory work and helped to win the Second World War, and by doing so, paved the way for future generations.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Getting Home
programme.desc: In this film, Bomber Command personnel and a Luftwaffe pilot take the viewer through the frightening reality of fighting in the skies as they try to get a damaged bomber home.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Hitting Back
programme.desc: After surviving the German bombing campaign of British cities, RAF Bomber Command struck back against Germany. The devastating consequences of raids, for both for the young men in the skies and the people on the ground, are portrayed in this film.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Japan continues its suicidal resistance, and invading it looks costly. After 2 atomic bombs, the Emperor intervenes and stops the War. Stalin grabs territory in East Asia. The War is over, and the Atomic Era and the Cold War start.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: In 1945, Germany is crumbly on both fronts. The Western Allies cross the Rhine and take most of Germany, while the Red Army quickly advances into Berlin. After Hitler's suicide, Germany surrenders and is divided among the allied powers.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The Marines succeed in the "island hopping" strategy against suicidal resistance. The US Navy establishes supremacy, cutting off Japan.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The Western Allies secure supply routes that will allow them to enter Germany, and the Ardennes counter-offensive fails. The Red Army advances rapidly. The SS implements the Holocaust.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: After a careful campaign of disinformation that throws the German defenders off-guard, the Western Allies finally land on Normandy.France is liberated.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Their attack on the Soviet Union having failed, the German Army suffers a series of counter-offensives on the Eastern Front. Wehrmacht's losses are huge as the Soviets advance West.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Allies turn the tide in the Atlantic, where initially German U-Boats harass freely convoys to supply Britain. The route to bring American soldiers who will land on D-Day is clear.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Italy's failed attacks in the Mediterranean region draw in the Germans.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Japan attacks the USA on 7 Dec 1941. For the next 6 months, they continue to have successful attacks.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The German invasion of Russia from Operation Barbarossa on 22 June 1941 to Kursk on 5 July 1943.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Germany makes critical errors during the bombing of Britain.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Country after European country falls before the unstoppable German blitzkrieg.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The activities of nations after World War I that lead to World War II.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Racial State 1933-1934
programme.desc: The Racial State 1933-1934: President Hindenburg suspends freedom of speech and Hitler comes to power in 1933. The first concentration camps for political opponents are set up.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Hidden in Plain Sight 1935-1938
programme.desc: Hidden In Plain Sight 1935-1938: In 1934, Hitler's government is firmly in the saddle. Most Germans support Hitler's anti-Jewish policy and the regime's terror soon escalates.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Up in Flames 1936-1940
programme.desc: Up in Flames 1936-1940: At the end of 1939, the German Army invades Poland. Examine how Hitler succeeded in pushing through his rearmament and war plans relatively unhindered.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942
programme.desc: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942: In the shadow of the war, the Nazi regime gradually advances its "final solution to the Jewish problem", culminating in the Holocaust.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Genocide 1942-1944
programme.desc: Genocide 1942 - 1944: Along with Treblinka and Majdanek, Sobibor was one of the camps used in Operation Reinhard, in which the Nazis murdered almost two million people.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Armageddon 1943-1945
programme.desc: Armageddon 1943-1945: The defeat at Stalingrad in 1943 was the turning point of the war and convinced the Nazi leadership to intensify their terror and propaganda campaigns.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Reckoning 1945-1948
programme.desc: The Reckoning 1945-1948: In 1945, WWII was over but the violence had not ended. The survivors want to blame the Germans. The reckoning with National Socialism is ambivalent.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.
programme.desc: From the Protection Squadron to the SS State: Trace the rise to power of the SS as we examine several perpetrators. Who was recruited? And why was the SS attractive to men?
programme.sub-title: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: An agriculturalist by trade, he went on to lead the SS and tried to escape responsibility at the end of the war. Who was Heinrich Himmler?

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich
programme.desc: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich: More than any other Nazi leader, Heydrich was an orchestrator of mass murder, and was terrifyingly clinical in approach.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Waffen-SS
programme.desc: The Waffen-SS: Masqueraded as military excellence, the reality was very different. Recruits were poorly trained and remorse was nonexistent, as SS troops killed mercilessly.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The SS Death Head's Unit
programme.desc: The SS Death Head's Unit: Tasked with guarding concentration camps, this unit's actions knew no bounds, and, despite their heinous acts, still attended social gatherings.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945
programme.desc: Unrepentant: The SS and Its Myth After 1945: Drawing a line to the present, the atrocities of the SS are beyond all doubt, yet, there is a cult surrounding 'old comrades' today.
programme.sub-title: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: The Quest for the Holy Grail
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.
programme.sub-title: The Quest for the Holy Grail

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Into the Mountains (Tibet)
programme.desc: Revealing the work of a secret team of scientists and scholars established by SS leader Heinrich Himmler to scour the globe seeking the origins of the Aryan race and collect ancient artifacts.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Adolf Hitler
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler: The film explores the roots of Adolf Hitler and traces the story of his life from the town of his birth to his final days.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: Largely due to the SS which he led, Himmler, the unsuspecting killer, was the most powerful of all of Hitler's men.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Josef Goebbels
programme.desc: Josef Goebbels: A unique documentary looking at the role of Goebbels, a man from Hitler's inner circle.

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Julius Streicher
programme.desc: Julius Streicher: A look at the role of Julius Streicher in the Nazi regime. Streicher was responsible for much anti-Semitic propaganda

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Hermann Goering
programme.desc: Hermann Goering: Hermann Goering was the commander-in-chief of the Luftwaffe and Hitler's designated successor. This is his dark story.

programme.title: World's Greatest Bridges: The Iron Bridge, Shropshire

programme.title: World's Greatest Bridges: Sydney Harbour Bridge

programme.title: World's Greatest Bridges: Severn Bridge
programme.desc: Rob Bell reveals how the Severn Bridge was constructed.

programme.title: World's Greatest Bridges: Brooklyn Bridge
programme.desc: A tale of big money, corruption, ambition, death and tragedy.

programme.title: World's Greatest Bridges: The Millau Viaduct

programme.title: Linda Napolitano: The Alien Abduction of the Century
programme.desc: Linda Napolitano's 1989 alien abduction is the abduction case of the century.

programme.title: 27 Alien Encounters
programme.desc: Strange and bizarre UFO encounters abound, but recent Alien encounters by highly credible eyewitnesses are so unusual and perplexing that they challenge our understanding of physics and the Universe as we know it.

programme.title: The Hills' Abduction: The Zeta Reticuli Incident
programme.desc: Barney & Betty Hill's abduction and the Zeta reticuli incident explored.

programme.title: Hopkinsville: The Alien Goblins
programme.desc: A family fights off goblin-aliens in a mysterious encounter, sparking debates and investigations. Fear drives their actions.

programme.title: Aliens in the USSR

programme.desc: Objects shot down in US/Canada airspace. Pentagon feigns ignorance. Alien involvement?

programme.title: Alien Paranormal: Bigfoot, UFOs and the Men in Black
programme.desc: Are Bigfoot creatures traveling to earth in UFO's, and being covered-up by Men in Black? Experience terrifying, real events as documented by top authorities, including: Aliens attacking a house; Alien Abductions to create a hybrid race; vortexes and more!

programme.title: Ancient Engineers: Aliens On Earth

programme.title: Roswell: The Untold Truth

programme.title: Aliens on the Moon: The Truth Exposed

programme.title: Alien from Area 51

programme.title: Alien Reptilian Legacy
programme.desc: Researchers reveal the presence of a supreme and nefarious interdimensional intelligence that has been manipulating mankind for centuries. Interviews with experiencers and alien abductees expose a sinister agenda behind the alien presence on Earth.

programme.title: Kanehsatake 270 Years Of Resistance
programme.desc: In July 1990, a dispute over a proposed golf course to be built on Kanien'kéhaka (Mohawk) lands in Oka, Quebec, set the stage for an historic confrontation that would grab international headlines and sear itself into the Canadian consciousness.

programme.title: The Fate Of America
programme.desc: On Sept 13, 1759, the Battle of the Plains of Abraham sealed America's fate in 20 mins. 'The Fate of America' explores this myth, leaving French Canadians pondering defeat. Filmmaker Jacques Godbout's take unites Montcalm and Wolfe's descendants.

programme.title: Canada Vignettes June In Povungnituk - Quebec Arctic
programme.desc: On a beautiful summer’s day in Nunavik, a family enjoys the pleasures of berry picking and fishing as the sound of two Elders throat-singing fills the environment. Directed by Alanis Obomsawin as part of the Canada Vignettes series.

programme.title: The Railrodder
programme.desc: A screen short starring Buster Keaton, this is one of the last films of the comedian's long career. As "the railrodder" he crosses Canada from east to west on a railway track speeder. As might be expected, the film is full of sight gags.

programme.title: Voices Across The Water
programme.desc: ‘Voices Across the Water’ follows two master boat builders as they practise their art and find a way back to balance and healing.

programme.title: Boys Will Be Men
programme.desc: This film takes an inside look at the world of juvenile delinquency. We are shown the tough existence on the streets of Montréal, but it could be any city in North America. Some boys as young as ten years of age talk about their lives of crime.

programme.title: Last Chance
programme.desc: Last Chance by Paul Émile d’Entremont travels the world to tell the stories of five asylum seekers who flee their native countries to escape homophobic violence. Here in Canada, they face hurdles integrating into society and fear deportation.

programme.title: Twenty Years Of Feminist Filmmaking
programme.desc: A clip montage for presentation at the National Action Committee on the Status of Women to commemorate the 20th anniversary of Studio D and the National Action Committee.

programme.title: I Want To Be An Engineer
programme.desc: This film provides a lively introduction to the professional and personal lives of three female engineers--just a few of the growing number of women who are opting for "non-traditional" jobs.

programme.title: To A Safer Place
programme.desc: To a Safer Place" follows Shirley Turcotte's journey as an incest survivor. Returning to her past, she confronts family violence with courage. Her story inspires survivors to find healing and dignity through frank disclosures.

programme.title: Some American Feminists
programme.desc: A series of interviews, interspersed with newsreel footage, places the American feminist movement in a historical perspective. Six of the women who gave impetus to the movement discuss those issues that most concern them and which are still being debated.

programme.title: Unarchived
programme.desc: In community archives across British Columbia, local knowledge keepers are fighting for a more inclusive history through family photos, newspaper articles and deeply rooted memories.

programme.title: First Stories - Two Spirited
programme.desc: This short documentary presents the empowering story of Rodney "Geeyo" Poucette's struggle against prejudice in the Indigenous community as a two spirited person (gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender).

programme.title: Everybodys Children
programme.desc: They arrive underage and alone, often traumatized and seeking asylum in a country completely alien to their own. This documentary is a cinematic portrait of a year in the life of two such teenagers, Joyce and Sallieu.

programme.title: Adams World
programme.desc: Adam's World present a short lecture by Elizabeth Dodson Gray, a feminist theologian, environmentalist, and futurist. She speaks to us about the severity of our global environmental crisis, and analyzes the root cause of this crisis.

programme.title: Under The Willow Tree Pioneer Chinese Women In Canada
programme.desc: Explore the untold history of Chinese Canadian women, from their courageous journeys to the challenges they faced in Canada. Through photos, recollections, and narration by Dora Nipp, this film captures their resilience and cultural legacy.

programme.title: Royal Journey
programme.desc: A documentary account of the five-week visit of Princess Elizabeth and the Duke of Edinburgh to Canada and the United States in the fall of 1951.

programme.title: Romance De Natal Arranjado
programme.desc: A Mandy descobre uma copia velha de "Um Conto de Natal" de Charles Dickens e uma carta de 70 anos para Papai Noel junto com uma moeda de muito valor.

programme.title: O Esquadrão do Papai Noel
programme.desc: Allie, uma professora de arte desempregada, aceita um trabalho no Esquadrão do Papai Noel para ajudar um viúvo rico e suas filhas a redescobrirem a magia do Natal. Enquanto tenta animar o espírito natalino, Allie é recompensada com o amor.

programme.title: A Rainha do Natal
programme.desc: Ashley Mackenzie encontra Ben, um recém-chegado que também ama o feriado. Vendo-o como rival no início, ela percebe que juntos podem criar um Natal ainda mais especial, unindo forças e celebrando o verdadeiro espírito natalino.

programme.title: Dançando No Natal
programme.desc: Olívia, professora de ballet, escolhe a talentosa Lily como protagonista do espetáculo de Natal "O Quebra-Nozes" e acaba se apaixonando pelo pai dela, Michael, um bombeiro atraente. Com a ajuda dele, Olívia tentará salvar seu estúdio de dança.

programme.title: Tesouros de Família
programme.desc: Uma titereira falida volta para casa nas férias e se envolve em uma caça ao tesouro com sua melhor amiga obcecada por paintball, sua avó dançarina de tango e um namorado de infância.

programme.title: O Natal de James & Bob
programme.desc: Um músico de rua em dificuldades se vê alvo de uma investigação de bemestar animal que ameaça levar seu amado gato no Natal.

programme.title: Um Ano Depois Daquele Natal
programme.desc: Na sequência de “Eu Vou Casar Nesse Natal”, um ano se passou desde o noivado entre Marci e Blair. Mas, com o grande dia se aproximando, Marci tem trabalhado tanto que mal conseguiu planejar seu casamento.

programme.title: Uma Viagem Para Paris
programme.desc: Lucas, um rico empresário francês, vai a Montana para uma proposta de negócio muito atraente. Lá, ele conhece Robin, se apaixona e a leva para Paris em uma incrível aventura de Natal. Mas será que os negócios acabarão com esse romance?

programme.title: Um Conto De Fadas Nas Montanhas
programme.desc: A pediatra Tasha Mason está focada em manter as crianças de sua enfermaria o mais saudáveis possível. Mas quando o belo Príncipe Alexander Cavalieri quebra a perna em uma pista de esqui, Tasha é forçada a cuidar de um mimado membro da realeza.

programme.title: Um conto de fadas nas Montanhas: Entrando para a realeza
programme.desc: É Natal novamente e a Dra. Tasha está a caminho para encontrar o Príncipe Alexander em St. Savarre.

programme.title: Christmas With Tucker
programme.desc: Tras la muerte de su padre, un niño forma un vínculo especial con el perro de un vecino y aprende a ser un hombre ayudando a sus abuelos durante una tormenta invernal.

programme.title: Bailey: Un héroe de Navidad
programme.desc: Es "tiempo de Navidad" y Bailey preocupado de que no recibirá regalos porque ha sido un mal perrito, aprende acerca de un misterioso indio nativo americano que puede ser capaz de hacer que sus deseos se hagan realidad.

programme.title: Los 3 Mosqueperros
programme.desc: ¡Ladrones se han marchado con todos los regalos y decoraciones de la familia y es hora de que los Tres Dogates se unan! El hambriento Barkos, el mago de raza pura Wagos y el amante de la aventura Arfamis emprenden un viaje para detectar a los malos.

programme.title: Mi Dulce Navidad
programme.desc: Sadie, una exitosa ejecutiva de marketing, es hija de los dueños de una chocolatería tradicional. Cuando decide pasar la Navidad con su familia, descubre que sus padres planean vender la tienda, poniendo en riesgo su sueño de heredarla algún día.

programme.title: The Christmas Candle
programme.desc: Un pastor que ha sufrido una pérdida personal acepta un puesto en un pueblo que cree en una vela milagrosa de Navidad, la cual se esfuerza por abolir.

programme.title: Una Navidad Encantada
programme.desc: Hugo, de doce años, sigue creyendo en los elfos, pero sus compañeros de clase se burlan de él y decide madurar. Pero cuando su familia se va de vacaciones de Navidad, descubre que los elfos viven en el hotel. Hugo puede lanzarse a la aventura.

programme.title: Las navidades de Pete
programme.desc: Petes Christmas es una película para televisión protagonizada por Zachary Gordon y Bailee Madison. Un niño se encuentra en el centro de atención inesperado cuando se da cuenta de que el terrible día de Navidad de su familia sigue repitiéndose.

programme.title: La Navidad de James & Bob
programme.desc: James Bowen es objeto de una investigación sobre el bienestar de los animales que amenaza con llevarse a su amado gato, Bob, en Navidad.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Una navidad para recordar
programme.desc: Sebastián, quien odia la Navidad y enfrenta su primer año sin sus hijos después de un divorcio, decide pasar la temporada con su madre Ángela, quien padece de Alzheimer.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: Christmas With Tucker
programme.desc: Tras la muerte de su padre, un niño forma un vínculo especial con el perro de un vecino y aprende a ser un hombre ayudando a sus abuelos durante una tormenta invernal.

programme.title: Bailey: Un héroe de Navidad
programme.desc: Es "tiempo de Navidad" y Bailey preocupado de que no recibirá regalos porque ha sido un mal perrito, aprende acerca de un misterioso indio nativo americano que puede ser capaz de hacer que sus deseos se hagan realidad.

programme.title: Los 3 Mosqueperros
programme.desc: ¡Ladrones se han marchado con todos los regalos y decoraciones de la familia y es hora de que los Tres Dogates se unan! El hambriento Barkos, el mago de raza pura Wagos y el amante de la aventura Arfamis emprenden un viaje para detectar a los malos.

programme.title: Mi Dulce Navidad
programme.desc: Sadie, una exitosa ejecutiva de marketing, es hija de los dueños de una chocolatería tradicional. Cuando decide pasar la Navidad con su familia, descubre que sus padres planean vender la tienda, poniendo en riesgo su sueño de heredarla algún día.

programme.title: The Christmas Candle
programme.desc: Un pastor que ha sufrido una pérdida personal acepta un puesto en un pueblo que cree en una vela milagrosa de Navidad, la cual se esfuerza por abolir.

programme.title: Una Navidad Encantada
programme.desc: Hugo, de doce años, sigue creyendo en los elfos, pero sus compañeros de clase se burlan de él y decide madurar. Pero cuando su familia se va de vacaciones de Navidad, descubre que los elfos viven en el hotel. Hugo puede lanzarse a la aventura.

programme.title: Las navidades de Pete
programme.desc: Petes Christmas es una película para televisión protagonizada por Zachary Gordon y Bailee Madison. Un niño se encuentra en el centro de atención inesperado cuando se da cuenta de que el terrible día de Navidad de su familia sigue repitiéndose.

programme.title: La Navidad de James & Bob
programme.desc: James Bowen es objeto de una investigación sobre el bienestar de los animales que amenaza con llevarse a su amado gato, Bob, en Navidad.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Una navidad para recordar
programme.desc: Sebastián, quien odia la Navidad y enfrenta su primer año sin sus hijos después de un divorcio, decide pasar la temporada con su madre Ángela, quien padece de Alzheimer.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.title: Conciertos Por Stingray

programme.title: Christmas With Tucker
programme.desc: Tras la muerte de su padre, un niño forma un vínculo especial con el perro de un vecino y aprende a ser un hombre ayudando a sus abuelos durante una tormenta invernal.

programme.title: Bailey: Un héroe de Navidad
programme.desc: Es "tiempo de Navidad" y Bailey preocupado de que no recibirá regalos porque ha sido un mal perrito, aprende acerca de un misterioso indio nativo americano que puede ser capaz de hacer que sus deseos se hagan realidad.

programme.title: Los 3 Mosqueperros
programme.desc: ¡Ladrones se han marchado con todos los regalos y decoraciones de la familia y es hora de que los Tres Dogates se unan! El hambriento Barkos, el mago de raza pura Wagos y el amante de la aventura Arfamis emprenden un viaje para detectar a los malos.

programme.title: Mi Dulce Navidad
programme.desc: Sadie, una exitosa ejecutiva de marketing, es hija de los dueños de una chocolatería tradicional. Cuando decide pasar la Navidad con su familia, descubre que sus padres planean vender la tienda, poniendo en riesgo su sueño de heredarla algún día.

programme.title: The Christmas Candle
programme.desc: Un pastor que ha sufrido una pérdida personal acepta un puesto en un pueblo que cree en una vela milagrosa de Navidad, la cual se esfuerza por abolir.

programme.title: Una Navidad Encantada
programme.desc: Hugo, de doce años, sigue creyendo en los elfos, pero sus compañeros de clase se burlan de él y decide madurar. Pero cuando su familia se va de vacaciones de Navidad, descubre que los elfos viven en el hotel. Hugo puede lanzarse a la aventura.

programme.title: Las navidades de Pete
programme.desc: Petes Christmas es una película para televisión protagonizada por Zachary Gordon y Bailee Madison. Un niño se encuentra en el centro de atención inesperado cuando se da cuenta de que el terrible día de Navidad de su familia sigue repitiéndose.

programme.title: La Navidad de James & Bob
programme.desc: James Bowen es objeto de una investigación sobre el bienestar de los animales que amenaza con llevarse a su amado gato, Bob, en Navidad.

programme.title: Enchanted Christmas
programme.desc: Cuando se fue de Utah como una joven viuda, Laura Trudeau dejó atrás a su padre, su amor por la danza y una vieja angustia.

programme.title: Una navidad para recordar
programme.desc: Sebastián, quien odia la Navidad y enfrenta su primer año sin sus hijos después de un divorcio, decide pasar la temporada con su madre Ángela, quien padece de Alzheimer.

programme.title: Una Noche Especial
programme.desc: Catherine y Robert son unos adultos mayores que nunca pensaron que podían encontrar algo increíble entre ellos. Su encuentro es una noche especial, siendo esto el inicio de una relación para vivir una segunda oportunidad de sentir verdadero amor.

programme.desc: Seit den späten 60er-Jahren ist Howard Carpendale regelmäßiger Gast in den Single- und Albumcharts in Deutschland. Bei GoldStar TV sehen Sie einen Konzertklassiker aus der Cottbusser Stadthalle von 2001. "Alles OK" hieß damals das Motto. Charmant und gut gelaunt wie eh und je stand Howard Carpendale dort auf der Bühne und präsentierte seine großen, zeitlosen Hits.

programme.title: Helden der Evolution
programme.desc: Sie sind geschmeidig, anmutig und schnell – das gilt nicht nur für die berühmten Großkatzen. Auch die meist scheuen und im Verborgenen jagenden Kleinkatzen haben mehr zu bieten als auffällige Fellmuster, scharfe Zähne und Krallen. Ihr Verhalten ist verblüffend vielfältig. Willkommen in der spannenden Welt der Geparden, Pumas, Jaguarundis, Ozelote und Rotluchse

programme.title: Helden der Evolution
programme.desc: Stromlinienförmig, anpassungsfähig, bisweilen tödlich und oftmals missverstanden: All dies trifft auf die Herrscher der Meere zu, die Haie. Die Familie der Haie umfasst mit über 500 Arten weit mehr als die „üblichen Verdächtigen“. Über die Hälfte von ihnen ist weniger als einen Meter lang, viele zudem scheu und harmlos. Dieser Tauchgang zu den faszinierenden Unterwasserjägern hat es in sich.

programme.title: Nigel Marvens wilde Philippinen
programme.desc: Die 15. größte Insel der Welt, aber die größte der Philippinen. Ein Land der Kontraste Von der Zersiedelung der Hauptstadt Manila bis hin zu riesigen versteckten Wäldern, den artenreichsten Riffen der Welt und einem Dutzend aktiver Vulkane, die die Skyline dominieren. Nigel trifft auf die außergewöhnlichen Kreaturen, die in diesen Landschaften leben.

programme.title: Wilde Schönheiten: Türkei
programme.desc: Im Mittleren Osten trifft Ost auf West, Wälder treffen auf Wüsten, die Tierwelt ist erstaunlich. Die weiten Landschaften der Türkei reichen von schneebedeckten Bergen zu Korallenriffen. Auch die anderen Länder sind alle einzigartig.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Die am meisten verbreitete Beziehung zwischen Lebewesen ist die von Räuber und Opfer. Aber es gibt auch andere, zum Beispiel gewaltfreie Beziehungen und viele andere, die für beide Seiten von Nutzen sind. Manchmal bleiben Tiere unterschiedlicher Gattungen ihr ganzes Leben zusammen.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Wir stehen alle auf irgendjemandes Speiseplan. Deshalb hat sich die in der Natur ausgebildete Spezialisierung auf eine bestimmte Beute und Nahrung auf so faszinierende Art weiterentwickelt. Fressen, ähnlich wie Sex, bereitet allen Tieren Freude, wenngleich in geringerer Intensivität.

programme.desc: Jeremy Wade sucht in Brasilien nach einem Fisch, der bereits drei Cowboys getötet hat.

programme.desc: Extremangler Jeremy Wade begibt sich auf der Suche nach einem Killerfisch tief nach Mittelamerika.

programme.title: Die Rückkehr zum afrikanischen Tigersalmler
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade begibt sich auf die Suche nach dem grausamen und fleischfressenden Tigerfisch.

programme.title: Der Riesenwels
programme.desc: Der Biologe und Extremangler Jeremy Wade geht den Gerüchten über einen menschenfressenden Wels nach.

programme.title: Der australische Süßwassersägerochen
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade ist im australischen Outback unterwegs, um den seltenen Süßwassersägerochen zu fangen.

programme.title: Die Wale der Azoren
programme.desc: Vulkanische Kräfte haben mitten im Atlantik grandiose Landschaften geformt. Die Azoren erheben sich aus rund 3.000 Meter Meerestiefe in die Höhe und ragen mehrere hundert, an einigen Stellen sogar über 2.000 Meter aus dem Wasser heraus. Der Atlantik bietet hier dank warmer Wasserströmungen zahllosen Meeresbewohnern reichlich Nahrung und ist ein Paradies für Wale und Delfine.

programme.title: David und die Drachen
programme.desc: Komodowarane sind die weltweit größten Echsen und erinnern an Drachen aus alten Geschichten. Die Riesenechsen leben seit etwa vier Millionen Jahren auf der Erde, wurden aber erst vor 100 Jahren wissenschaftlich beschrieben. Heute gibt es noch rund 2.500 frei lebende Komodowarane. Die Inseln des Nationalparks Komodo sind ihre letzten Rückzugsorte.

programme.title: Die Rattenfänger von Kambodscha
programme.desc: Der Tonle Sap in Kambodscha ist der größte See Südostasiens. Familie Krouy lebt von der Fischerei. Doch jetzt, Anfang September, hat der See seinen Wasserhöchststand erreicht. Die Netze reichen nicht mehr bis zum Grund. Es wird immer schwieriger, Fische zu fangen. Deshalb gehen Sey Ha und seine Freunde auf Ratten-Jagd. Mit dem Verkauf der Ratten können sie in der Regenzeit Geld verdienen.

programme.title: Australien
programme.desc: Koala-Baby Neil lebt seit einigen Wochen bei seinen Pflegeeltern, einem älteren Ehepaar, im Badeort Port Macquarie an der Ostküste Australiens. Das Waisenjunge wurde ohne Mutter gefunden. In Port Macquarie steht auch das erste Koala-Hospital Australiens. Ob Brandwunden oder Infektionen - seit 1973 finden hier alle verletzten, kranken oder verwaisten Koalas der Region ein vorübergehendes Zuhause

programme.title: Die Glücksvögel von Buthan
programme.desc: Im Königreich Buthan, mitten im Himalaya, gelten Kraniche als Vögel des Glücks. Das Phobjikha-Tal, tief im Inneren des Landes, ist ihr Winterquartier. Seit Monaten war kein Ruf der Tiere zu hören. Der elfjährige Karma wartet schon sehnsüchtig auf die Zugvögel. Er ist ein wahrer Kranich-Fan. Dann sind die beliebten Kraniche endlich da!

programme.title: Russlands Zirkusschule auf Tour
programme.desc: Am sonst so stillen Ufer des Seligersees zwischen Moskau und Sankt Petersburg ist einiges los. Hier bringen die jungen Studenten der Moskauer Zirkusschule Trubel in das Leben der Dorfbewohner. Diese Reportage begleitet die junge Artistentruppe auf ihrer Sommerreise.

programme.title: Die Millon-Dollar-Hirsche
programme.desc: Am Fuße des Altai-Gebirges, zwischen Russland, China und der Mongolei, leben die Maral-Hirsche, deren majestätisches Geweih in der fernöstlichen Medizin ein beliebtes Heilmittel ist. Sibirische Wildhüter treiben die Tiere deshalb in den Sommermonaten zusammen, um ihnen ihren Kopfschmuck abzusägen, was bei aller Erfahrung nicht immer gelingt. Das letzte Mal haben wir ungefähr 500 Marale inspiziert. Davon hab ich 60 ausgewählt, die wir dann beschnitten haben?, sagt Sasha Tcherepanov, der gemeinsam mit seinen Brüdern je Saison 2500 Hirsche unter die Lupe nehmen muss. Es ist Juni im Hirschrevier Sauzar, und den Wildhütern bleibt für die Geweihernte nicht mehr viel Zeit. Denn jetzt ist der Kopfschmuck der Marale zwar ausgewachsen, jedoch noch mit Basthaaren überzogen und durchblutet - ein Zustand, in dem die Geweihe am wertvollsten sind. Mehrere Hundert Dollar kostet ein Geweih. Für die Abnehmer, die hauptsächlich aus Südkorea anreisen, ist der Preis kein Problem. Schließlich finden russische Bastgeweihe in ihrem Heimatland einen reißenden Absatz: In hauchdünne Scheiben geschnitten, verwenden sie Ärzte und Krankhäuser häufig als Teebeimischung. Eine schmerzlindernde Wirkung versprechen sich Sasha und seine Brüder außerdem von dem Blutsud, der nach dem Kochen der Maral-Geweihe übri ...

programme.title: Kalmückien
programme.desc: Sanan Matvenov ist erst 26 Jahre alt, doch seit seinem 13. Lebensjahr studiert er die Lehre Buddhas. Mit sieben anderen Mönchen im Alter von 16 bis 26 Jahren lebt er im Goldenen Tempel von Elista, der Hauptstadt Kalmückiens. Im südeuropäischen Teil Russlands, nordwestlich des kaspischen Meeres, lebt das einzige mehrheitlich buddhistische Volk Europas: die Kalmücken. Ihre autonome Republik besteht überwiegend aus Steppe und ist mit knapp vier Bewohnern pro Quadratkilometer extrem dünn besiedelt. Erst seit dem Zusammenbruch der Sowjetunion darf hier der Buddhismus wieder offizieall ausgelebt werden.Planet Weltweit hat den jungen Mönch durch das weitgehend unbekannte Land begleitet.

programme.title: Die scharfen Klingen der Auvergne
programme.desc: Einst gehörte es in die Hosentasche jedes Mannes, in Frankreich wie anderswo, handgefertigt und unverwüstlich, ein markanter und eigenwilliger Alltagsgegenstand: Das Taschenmesser. Das legendäre und unverkennbare Laguiole-Messer hat hier in Zentralfrankreich seine Wurzeln - und seine Meister. Planet Weltweit schaut in die Werkstätten der berühmten Messermeister in einer der atemberaubendsten Regionen Frankreichs.

programme.title: Stilikone Panamahut
programme.desc: Der Panamahut ist der wohl berühmteste Hut der Welt. Dennoch ist über seine wahre Herkunft - er kommt aus Ecuador, nicht aus Panama - und über die aufwendige Kunst des Strohhutflechtens wenig bekannt. Die feinsten Panama Hüte werden auch heute noch von Königshäuptern getragen und Prominente schmücken sich gerne damit. Sie bezahlen Preise von bis zu 10.000 Euro pro Hut, weil sie die Einzigartigkeit und Qualität zu schätzen wissen. Umso erstaunlicher erscheint es da, das die jahrhundertealte Tradition des Strohhutflechtens in Ecuador völlig zu verschwinden droht. Planet Weltweit will das Geheimnis des Panamahutes lüften. Ein Film über die unbekannten Hutflechter von Ecuador.

programme.title: Marokko, die andere Seite des Paradieses
programme.desc: Die andere Seite des Paradieses?Ein Film von Thorsten NiemannFrüher Morgen in der Medina von F?s - der schönsten und größten Stadt von ganz Marokko. In einer kleinen Wohnung sitzt Simohamed El Ouzzani mit seiner Frau Nadja beim Frühstück. Zeit zum Essen wird der schmächtige Mann mit den lebhaften, dunklen Augen an diesem Tag nicht mehr haben. Simohamed ist einer der letzten traditionellen Gerber von F?s und der beste, wie er selbst sagt. Es ist ein Knochenjob, doch Simohamed liebt ihn, zumal das traditionelle Gerberhandwerk Marokkos vom Aussterben bedroht ist. Die Dokumentation ist in die Medina von F?s eingetaucht und hat sich an die Fersen eines bemerkenswerten Mannes geheftet.

programme.title: Bishnoi, Tierliebe bis in den Tod
programme.desc: Vor über 500 Jahren gründete ein indischer Guru die Gemeinschaft der Bishnoi, einem Volk, das sich dem Schutz allen Lebens verschrieben hat - und in enger Verbindung mit Pflanzen und Tieren lebt. Die Heimat ihrer Nachkommen ist noch immer die Wüste Rajasthans. Dort verteidigen die Bishnoi bis heute ihre traditionellen Regeln gegen die Einflüsse der modernen Welt, notfalls unter Einsatz ihres Lebens.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

programme.title: Astrud Gilberto & Dizzy Gillespie
programme.sub-title: Gilberto, Gillespie & Skymasters - North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1982, Dutch big band The Skymasters accompanied monumental jazz trumpet legend Dizzy Gillespie and the Brazilian bossa nova singer Astrud Gilberto at the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague.

programme.title: Philip Catherine, Jean-Louis Rassinfosse & Chet Baker
programme.sub-title: Jazz a la Grand Place Chet Baker Trio
programme.desc: Two top-tier Belgian musicians – guitarist Philip Catherine and bassist Jean-Louis Rassinfosse – accompany American jazz trumpeter and vocalist Chet Baker during this 1985 performance at the beautiful Brussels Jazz Club, located on the Grand-Place, the Belgian capital's central square. The trio plays Charlie Mariano's “Crystal Bells”, the title track of their acclaimed 1983 album. Other songs played during this legendary concert include “Down” and “How Deep is the Ocean”.

programme.title: John Coltrane
programme.sub-title: I want to talk about you
programme.desc: Explore the music of one of the most influential and innovative saxophonists in jazz history: John Coltrane! Immerse yourself in this collection of remarkable performances from the early 1960s that showcase Coltrane's unparalleled artistry and unique sound during a transformative period in the artist's career. Recorded in various European cities, Coltrane is seen playing the songs “Autumn Leaves”, “Hackensack”, “My Favorite Things”, “I Want To Talk About You”, “Vigil”, and “Naima”. Tune in and experience why the music of John Coltrane has touched the lives of so many!

programme.title: Thelonious Monk

programme.title: Freddie Hubbard, Al Grey, Alvin Batiste & Al Casey
programme.sub-title: Freddie Hubbard & The Satchmo Legacy Live in 1987
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. This concert of Freddie Hubbard and the Satchmo Legacy in 1987, highlights the bebop legend's classic style and silky tone. Hubbard is an American jazz trumpeter whose unmistakable and influential tone contributed to new perspectives for modern jazz and bebop. He was also a well-known part of Art Blakey and the Jazz Messengers and is primarily known for playing bebop, hard bop, and post-bop styles from the early '60s onwards.

programme.title: Ahmad Jamal Trio
programme.sub-title: Ahmad Jamal Trio - North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1989, legendary jazz pianist Ahmad Jamal brought his trio to the North Sea Jazz Festival. Accompanied by James Cammack on bass and David Bowler on drums, Jamal showcased his excellence.

programme.title: Louis Armstrong
programme.desc: Following a highly successful small-group jazz concert at New York Town Hall on May 17, 1947, Armstrong's manager Joe Glaser dissolved the Armstrong big band on August 13, 1947 and established a six-piece small group. This group was called the All Stars, and in 1964 Louis Armstrong recorded his biggest-selling record, Hello, Dolly! He made assorted television appearances, especially in the 1950s and 1960s – the recorded film was a TV Show in Australia when Armstrong was at the peak of his career. Armstrong kept up his busy tour schedule until a few years before his death in 1971. He also toured Africa, Europe, and Asia under sponsorship of the US State Department with great success, earning the nickname ‘Ambassador Satch'.

programme.sub-title: Martha Argerich – A Birthday Celebration III
programme.desc: On the occasion of her 80th birthday, Argentinian pianist Martha Argerich explored chamber music repertoire in this wonderful concert, recorded at Château de Chantilly, France. The ‘Grande Dame' of the piano is joined by various renowned artists, including pianists Lily Maisky and Iddo Bar-Shaï, violinists Tedi Papavrami and Akiko Suwanai, her daughter Lyda Chen-Argerich on viola, and cellist Mischa Maisky. On the program are Felix Mendelssohn's Piano Trio No. 1 in D minor, Op. 49 Leoš Janáček's Violin Sonata Franz Schubert's Rondo in A major, D. 951 and Johannes Brahms's Piano Quartet No. 3 in C minor, Op. 60. These performances were recorded on May 4 and June 13, 2021.

programme.title: Zhu Xiao-Mei
programme.desc: Chinese pianist Zhu Xiao-Mei performs J. S. Bach's Goldberg Variations (BWV 988) at the Leipzig Bach Festival. This June 2014 concert was recorded at St. Thomas Church, where Bach spent most time of his career as 'Thomaskantor', the musical director of the Thomanerchor church choir. The Goldberg Variations consist of one aria and a set of 30 variations. The work was first published in 1741 and was named after harpsichordist Johann Gottlieb Goldberg. In contrast to melodic variations on a theme, the Goldberg Variations do not follow the melody, but rather use the aria's bass line and chord progression. Every third variation in the series of 30 is a canon that follows an ascending pattern. The Goldberg Variations are among Bach's most celebrated works, which gained an even larger audience thanks to Glenn Gould's legendary recordings of the work in 1955 and 1981.

programme.title: Glass Marcano, Orchestre Symphonique Région Centre-Val de Loire/Tours & Stéphanie-Marie Degand
programme.sub-title: Beethoven Violin Concerto & Bizet Symphony in C
programme.desc: Young Venezuelan conductor Glass Marcano is a rising star. Having played in various local youth and symphony orchestras as a violinist, her first experience conducting an ensemble followed in 2012. In September 2020, she won the Orchestra Prize at La Maestra Competition – the first orchestra direction contest for women – held in Paris. In this concert, recorded at Opéra de Tours in February 2021, Marcano leads the Orchestre Symphonique Région Centre-Val de Loire/Tours in performances of two Romantic masterpieces. The program opens with Ludwig van Beethoven's Violin Concerto in D major, Op. 61, featuring Stéphanie-Marie Degand as the soloist. This piece is one of the most important works in its genre. The program concludes with Georges Bizet's 1855 Symphony in C major, written when the composer was only 17 years old.

programme.title: David Grimal & Les Dissonances
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Symphony No. 4 in B-flat major, Op. 60
programme.desc: Les Dissonances is a collective of artists founded by violinist David Grimal in 2004. The conductorless ensemble consists of musicians from the most prestigious European orchestras, international soloists, and young talents. In this performance, Les Dissonances perform Ludwig van Beethoven's Symphony No. 4 in B-flat major, Op. 60. Count Franz von Oppersdorff, who adored Beethoven's Symphony No. 2, offered the composer a large sum to write a similar work. Completed in the autumn of 1806, the symphony's first performance was at a private concert in Vienna in March of 1807. Symphony No. 4 is often overshadowed by its revolutionary predecessor and successor. With its lightweight and cheerful nature, Symphony No. 4 contrasts with the two aforementioned works. This performance was recorded at Opéra de Dijon, France, in 2013.

Unfortunately there are not that vibrant anymore today. Coral reefs have suffered from the rise of water temperature, rise in acidity, destructive fishing methods and severe storms caused by climate change." - Peter Schneider. programme.title: Kinderstube Wildnis Bei den Löwen
programme.desc: Eine alleinerziehende Löwin hat es nicht leicht in Afrikas Savannen. Löwen-Mama Nyota hat keine Beschützer und muss für sich und ihren fünf Monate alten Sohn Moja ganz alleine sorgen. Vor der Regenzeit sind Beutetiere spärlich und die besten Reviere von großen Löwenrudeln besetzt. Auf sich alleine gestellt, muss Nyota zwischen ihrem knurrenden Magen und dem Schutz des Kleinen abwägen. Es gelingt ihr kaum, sich einmal satt zu essen. Entweder die Jagdversuche bleiben erfolglos oder Hyänen machen ihr das mühsam erlegte Wild nach wenigen Bissen streitig. Alleine hat sie den Aasfressern kaum etwas entgegen zu setzen. Um Moja nicht in Gefahr zu bringen, verzichtet sie jedoch auf einen Kampf und überlässt ihren Fang der gierigen Meute. Berührende Szenen zeigen, wie das Duo trotz der immer weiter schwindenden Kräfte auch in den härtesten Wochen zusammenhält. Die Rettung der kleinen Familie naht in Form der heraufziehenden Gnu-Herden.

programme.title: Tiere vor der Kamera: Die Nächte der Kröten
programme.desc: Der Klassiker „Tiere vor der Kamera“ wurde von 1974 bis 2016 für den Bayerischen Rundfunk produziert. Die mehrfach preisgekrönte Serie von Ernst Arendt und Hans Schweiger lässt uns Tiere hautnah erleben – und mit ihnen lachen.

programme.title: Wunderwelt Schweiz – Die Jura-Region
programme.desc: Die Schweiz braucht sich hinter den exotischen Naturparadiesen dieser Welt nicht zu verstecken. So klein sie auch sein mag - ihre abwechslungsreiche Natur ist einzigartig und steckt voller Wunder.

programme.title: Die Wale der Azoren
programme.desc: Vulkanische Kräfte haben mitten im Atlantik grandiose Landschaften geformt. Die Azoren erheben sich aus rund 3.000 Meter Meerestiefe in die Höhe und ragen mehrere hundert, an einigen Stellen sogar über 2.000 Meter aus dem Wasser heraus. Der Atlantik bietet hier dank warmer Wasserströmungen zahllosen Meeresbewohnern reichlich Nahrung und ist ein Paradies für Wale und Delfine.

programme.title: David und die Drachen
programme.desc: Komodowarane sind die weltweit größten Echsen und erinnern an Drachen aus alten Geschichten. Die Riesenechsen leben seit etwa vier Millionen Jahren auf der Erde, wurden aber erst vor 100 Jahren wissenschaftlich beschrieben. Heute gibt es noch rund 2.500 frei lebende Komodowarane. Die Inseln des Nationalparks Komodo sind ihre letzten Rückzugsorte.

programme.title: Die Rattenfänger von Kambodscha
programme.desc: Der Tonle Sap in Kambodscha ist der größte See Südostasiens. Familie Krouy lebt von der Fischerei. Doch jetzt, Anfang September, hat der See seinen Wasserhöchststand erreicht. Die Netze reichen nicht mehr bis zum Grund. Es wird immer schwieriger, Fische zu fangen. Deshalb gehen Sey Ha und seine Freunde auf Ratten-Jagd. Mit dem Verkauf der Ratten können sie in der Regenzeit Geld verdienen.

programme.title: Australien
programme.desc: Koala-Baby Neil lebt seit einigen Wochen bei seinen Pflegeeltern, einem älteren Ehepaar, im Badeort Port Macquarie an der Ostküste Australiens. Das Waisenjunge wurde ohne Mutter gefunden. In Port Macquarie steht auch das erste Koala-Hospital Australiens. Ob Brandwunden oder Infektionen - seit 1973 finden hier alle verletzten, kranken oder verwaisten Koalas der Region ein vorübergehendes Zuhause

programme.title: Die Glücksvögel von Buthan
programme.desc: Im Königreich Buthan, mitten im Himalaya, gelten Kraniche als Vögel des Glücks. Das Phobjikha-Tal, tief im Inneren des Landes, ist ihr Winterquartier. Seit Monaten war kein Ruf der Tiere zu hören. Der elfjährige Karma wartet schon sehnsüchtig auf die Zugvögel. Er ist ein wahrer Kranich-Fan. Dann sind die beliebten Kraniche endlich da!

programme.title: Russlands Zirkusschule auf Tour
programme.desc: Am sonst so stillen Ufer des Seligersees zwischen Moskau und Sankt Petersburg ist einiges los. Hier bringen die jungen Studenten der Moskauer Zirkusschule Trubel in das Leben der Dorfbewohner. Diese Reportage begleitet die junge Artistentruppe auf ihrer Sommerreise.

programme.title: Die Millon-Dollar-Hirsche
programme.desc: Am Fuße des Altai-Gebirges, zwischen Russland, China und der Mongolei, leben die Maral-Hirsche, deren majestätisches Geweih in der fernöstlichen Medizin ein beliebtes Heilmittel ist. Sibirische Wildhüter treiben die Tiere deshalb in den Sommermonaten zusammen, um ihnen ihren Kopfschmuck abzusägen, was bei aller Erfahrung nicht immer gelingt. Das letzte Mal haben wir ungefähr 500 Marale inspiziert. Davon hab ich 60 ausgewählt, die wir dann beschnitten haben?, sagt Sasha Tcherepanov, der gemeinsam mit seinen Brüdern je Saison 2500 Hirsche unter die Lupe nehmen muss. Es ist Juni im Hirschrevier Sauzar, und den Wildhütern bleibt für die Geweihernte nicht mehr viel Zeit. Denn jetzt ist der Kopfschmuck der Marale zwar ausgewachsen, jedoch noch mit Basthaaren überzogen und durchblutet - ein Zustand, in dem die Geweihe am wertvollsten sind. Mehrere Hundert Dollar kostet ein Geweih. Für die Abnehmer, die hauptsächlich aus Südkorea anreisen, ist der Preis kein Problem. Schließlich finden russische Bastgeweihe in ihrem Heimatland einen reißenden Absatz: In hauchdünne Scheiben geschnitten, verwenden sie Ärzte und Krankhäuser häufig als Teebeimischung. Eine schmerzlindernde Wirkung versprechen sich Sasha und seine Brüder außerdem von dem Blutsud, der nach dem Kochen der Maral-Geweihe übri ...

programme.title: Kalmückien
programme.desc: Sanan Matvenov ist erst 26 Jahre alt, doch seit seinem 13. Lebensjahr studiert er die Lehre Buddhas. Mit sieben anderen Mönchen im Alter von 16 bis 26 Jahren lebt er im Goldenen Tempel von Elista, der Hauptstadt Kalmückiens. Im südeuropäischen Teil Russlands, nordwestlich des kaspischen Meeres, lebt das einzige mehrheitlich buddhistische Volk Europas: die Kalmücken. Ihre autonome Republik besteht überwiegend aus Steppe und ist mit knapp vier Bewohnern pro Quadratkilometer extrem dünn besiedelt. Erst seit dem Zusammenbruch der Sowjetunion darf hier der Buddhismus wieder offizieall ausgelebt werden.Planet Weltweit hat den jungen Mönch durch das weitgehend unbekannte Land begleitet.

programme.title: Die scharfen Klingen der Auvergne
programme.desc: Einst gehörte es in die Hosentasche jedes Mannes, in Frankreich wie anderswo, handgefertigt und unverwüstlich, ein markanter und eigenwilliger Alltagsgegenstand: Das Taschenmesser. Das legendäre und unverkennbare Laguiole-Messer hat hier in Zentralfrankreich seine Wurzeln - und seine Meister. Planet Weltweit schaut in die Werkstätten der berühmten Messermeister in einer der atemberaubendsten Regionen Frankreichs.

programme.title: Stilikone Panamahut
programme.desc: Der Panamahut ist der wohl berühmteste Hut der Welt. Dennoch ist über seine wahre Herkunft - er kommt aus Ecuador, nicht aus Panama - und über die aufwendige Kunst des Strohhutflechtens wenig bekannt. Die feinsten Panama Hüte werden auch heute noch von Königshäuptern getragen und Prominente schmücken sich gerne damit. Sie bezahlen Preise von bis zu 10.000 Euro pro Hut, weil sie die Einzigartigkeit und Qualität zu schätzen wissen. Umso erstaunlicher erscheint es da, das die jahrhundertealte Tradition des Strohhutflechtens in Ecuador völlig zu verschwinden droht. Planet Weltweit will das Geheimnis des Panamahutes lüften. Ein Film über die unbekannten Hutflechter von Ecuador.

programme.title: Marokko, die andere Seite des Paradieses
programme.desc: Die andere Seite des Paradieses?Ein Film von Thorsten NiemannFrüher Morgen in der Medina von F?s - der schönsten und größten Stadt von ganz Marokko. In einer kleinen Wohnung sitzt Simohamed El Ouzzani mit seiner Frau Nadja beim Frühstück. Zeit zum Essen wird der schmächtige Mann mit den lebhaften, dunklen Augen an diesem Tag nicht mehr haben. Simohamed ist einer der letzten traditionellen Gerber von F?s und der beste, wie er selbst sagt. Es ist ein Knochenjob, doch Simohamed liebt ihn, zumal das traditionelle Gerberhandwerk Marokkos vom Aussterben bedroht ist. Die Dokumentation ist in die Medina von F?s eingetaucht und hat sich an die Fersen eines bemerkenswerten Mannes geheftet.

programme.title: Bishnoi, Tierliebe bis in den Tod
programme.desc: Vor über 500 Jahren gründete ein indischer Guru die Gemeinschaft der Bishnoi, einem Volk, das sich dem Schutz allen Lebens verschrieben hat - und in enger Verbindung mit Pflanzen und Tieren lebt. Die Heimat ihrer Nachkommen ist noch immer die Wüste Rajasthans. Dort verteidigen die Bishnoi bis heute ihre traditionellen Regeln gegen die Einflüsse der modernen Welt, notfalls unter Einsatz ihres Lebens.

programme.title: Waschbären, unsere neuen Nachbarn?
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Ursprünglich stammen Waschbären aus Nordamerika. Inzwischen breiten sie sich auch in Europa aus. Da sie 2016 von der EU als invasiv, also als Gefahr für das Ökosystem eingestuft wurden, werden sie massiv bejagt. Die Berliner Tierärztin Dr. Mathilde Laininger engagiert sich für ein friedliches Miteinander zwischen Mensch und Waschbär.

Ambos se han enfrentado a una educación difícil y han triunfado. Ahora triunfan juntos. Este especial de una hora, que incluye una entrevista con el biógrafo Andrew Morton, investiga el trasfondo social que hace que este matrimonio aventurero parezca totalmente acorde con la moderna Familia Real británica. Explora las extraordinarias vidas de la actriz Meghan Markle, una poderosa defensora de los derechos de la mujer, y del Príncipe Harry, que ha roto con la camisa de fuerza real sin perder su dignidad real. Ochenta y dos años después de que un romance con una plebeya divorciada de Estados Unidos condujera a la abdicación de un Rey, este matrimonio real establece y confirma un revolucionario conjunto de valores británicos.

programme.title: Carter's W.A.R.
programme.desc: Carter's W.A.R. (Wild Animal Response) è la storia mai raccontata della ricerca di un uomo per salvare la sua patria, il continente più selvaggio e pericoloso del mondo, l'Africa. Dai bracconieri armati fino ai denti che massacrano gli elefanti per le loro zanne al massacro dei rinoceronti per i loro corni, la risorsa più preziosa dell'Africa è in pericolo. Può un uomo svelare la verità e fare la differenza? Guardate come Ivan Carter, detective della fauna selvatica e cacciatore professionista, vi porta all'interno della vera Africa, in prima linea nelle guerre scatenate contro la sua fauna selvatica.

programme.title: Wild Ones

programme.title: Desperate Hours
programme.desc: Quando la Terra si muove davvero, significa disastro su scala epica. Desperate Hours analizza la forza distruttiva dei terremoti e prende in esame il terremoto di Kathmandu del 2015 in Nepal, il terremoto del Sichuan del 2008 in Cina, dove si stima che 10.000 bambini siano rimasti intrappolati negli edifici scolastici crollati, il terremoto di Puerto Mont del 1960 in Cile, il terremoto di Port-au-Princ del 2010 ad Haiti e il terremoto del Kashmir del 2005 in Pakistan.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature
programme.desc: Avventuratevi nello stato balneare messicano di Veracruz, nel sud-ovest del Paese, e ammirate gli incredibili colori delle orchidee coltivate localmente. Scoprite come si coltiva la vaniglia e come si produce lo zucchero di canna. Per finire, assisteremo a uno straordinario rituale. In seguito, visiteremo le Isole Cayman, nei Caraibi. Le tre isole sono relativamente piccole, ma sono abitate da animali straordinari, tra cui tartarughe marine, simpatiche razze e altri tipi di pesci, oltre alle affascinanti iguane blu.

programme.title: Miracles of Nature
programme.desc: Oggi visiteremo tre straordinari angoli d'Europa alla ricerca di miracoli della natura. Per cominciare, ci avventureremo nella regione austriaca di Salisburgo. Un'area famosa per le Alpi e i Monti Tauri, ma anche perché è il luogo di nascita di Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart. Successivamente, ci sposteremo nell'avamposto sud-occidentale del vecchio continente, nella regione portoghese dell'Algarve. Per concludere, ammireremo la Corsica, l'isola francese della bellezza.

programme.title: 금빛 문양의 아름다움. 금박장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널우리나라 의복의 아름다움과 우아함을 한껏 더 담아내는 기술, ‘금박'. 금박장은 직물 위에 얇은 금박을 이용해 다양한 문양을 찍어내는 장인입니다. 세계적으로 관심이 높아지고 있는 한복에서 가장 아름다움을 극대화하는 금빛 문양이 만들어지는 과정과 소리를 함께 감상해봅시다. (김기호 / 국가무형문화재 금박장 보유자)

programme.title: 오감이 가득. 궁중병과 다과상
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널오감이 가득한 다과상을 만들어봐요! 쑥이 들어간 경단 쑥구리단자, 밀가루 반죽을 꼬아서 예쁘게 모양을 낸 한과 매작과와 소나무 꽃가루를 이용해 만든 전통음료인 송화밀수까지. 이번에는 청각 뿐만이 아니라 시각, 후각, 미각, 촉각 까지 담아보았습니다. (박영미 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)

programme.title: 혼을 담은 붓. 필장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널필장은 문방사우(文房四友)의 하나인 붓을 만드는 장인입니다. 붓은 털의 품질이 가장 중요하며 붓끝이 뾰족해야 하고 가지런해야 하며, 털 윗부분이 끈으로 잘 묶여서 둥근 것, 오래 써도 힘이 있어 한 획을 긋고 난 뒤에 붓털이 다시 일어나야 합니다. 수천번의 손길을 거쳐야 완성되는 전통 붓 제작과정을 함께 감상해 보시죠. (유필무 / 충북무형문화재 필장 보유자)

programme.title: 예술의 경지, 다회치기. 매듭장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널매듭장이란 끈목[多繒]을 사용하여 여러 종류의 매듭을 짓고, 술을 만드는 기술 또는 그러한 기술을 가진 장인입니다. 우리나라의 전통매듭은 단색의 끈목을 이용하여 모양을 맺고 아래에 술을 달아 비례미와 율동미를 추구한 것이 특징입니다. 매듭장의 실을 엮는 과정인 '다회치기'를 ASMR 버전으로 감상해 보시죠. (박선경 / 국가무형문화재 매듭장 전승교육사)

programme.title: 전통 무예, 활쏘기. 화살 만들기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널황학정은 1898년 활쏘기가 단순히 심신단련의 기예가 아닌 외세에도 꺾이지 않는 조선의 정신임을 백성들에게 널리 알리기 위해 고종 의지로 세워진 활터입니다. 화살이 만들어지며 나는 소리와 활을 쏘는 소리를 감상해보세요. (신동술 / 황학정 국궁전시관 관장)

programme.title: 천년의 종이를 만드는 마법. 한지뜨기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널한지는 고도의 기술과 장인의 오랜 경험을 바탕으로 완성됩니다. 닥나무를 베고, 찌고, 삶고, 말리고, 벗기고, 다시 삶고, 두들기고, 섞고, 뜨고, 말리는 99번의 손질 후 마지막 사람이 백번째로 만진다 하여 옛사람들은 한지를 '백지(百紙)'라 부르기도 하였습니다. 장인의 정성이 담겨있는 '한지뜨기' 과정을 만나보시죠. (안치용 / 국가무형문화재 한지장 보유자)

programme.title: 전통 금속활자 제조의 맥. 금속활자장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널금속활자는 활판인쇄를 하기 위해 쇠붙이를 녹여 주형에 부어 만든 각종 크기의 활자입니다. 금속활자 만드는 방법 중 모래를 활용해 만드는 주물사주조법(Metal Type-casting using Sand)을 통해 세계 최초로 금속활자를 만든 민족의 역사를 간직한 글자를 만드는 소리를 들어봅니다. (임인호 / 국가무형문화재 금속활자장 보유자)

programme.title: 전통을 담고 맛을 잇다. 장 담그기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널한국 음식의 맛은 장이 결정한다고 할 정도로 옛 조상들은 장맛이 좋지 않으면 좋은 재료를 사용해도 좋은 요리가 될 수 없다고 하였습니다. 콩 재배, 메주 만들기, 장 만들기, 장 가르기, 숙성과 발효 등으로 이어지는 중국이나 일본과 구별되는 우리나라의 독특한 제작과정을 영상으로 만나보세요. (이정숙 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)

programme.title: [조선왕릉 가을 숲길] 세조의 회한이 담긴 숲, 광릉
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널남양주의 광릉은 조선 제7대 왕 세조와 정희왕후가 잠들어있는 곳입니다. 이 광릉이 있는 광릉숲은 서울 여의도 면적의 30배 규모의 울창한 숲으로, 생태적 안정성과 종 다양성을 엿볼 수 있습니다. 산과 도로, 하천을 끼고 만들어진 광릉숲길을 함께 걸어봐요. ※ 남양주 광릉 (사적 제197호) / 조선왕릉 (2009년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [궁궐 속 비밀의 화원] 창덕궁 낙선재 후원 EP.2
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널낙선재는 헌종 대에 지어진 건물로, 사대부 주택의 형식을 따랐으나 궁궐 침전의 양식이 가미되었습니다. 때문에 다른 곳에서는 쉽게 찾아볼 수 없는 다양한 문양의 장식이 있어 조선 후기 건축의 축적된 기량을 엿볼 수 있죠. 일반인 비공개 지역인 창덕궁 낙선재 후원을 바라보며 휴식을 취해보세요. ※ 창덕궁 낙선재 (보물 1764호) / 창덕궁 (1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [창덕궁 봄꽃 개화 현장] 낙선재 뒷뜰, 돌배나무 풍경
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널창덕궁은 태종 때 건립된 조선왕조의 왕궁으로, 처음에는 경복궁의 이궁으로 지어졌지만 경복궁보다 더욱 오래 법궁의 역할을 해왔습니다. 특히 창덕궁 후원은 한국의 유일한 궁궐후원이라는 점에서 그 가치가 매우 높지요. 한국의 대표적인 정원인 창덕궁이 봄을 맞이하는 아름다운 모습을 감상해보세요! ※ 창덕궁 (사적 제122호, 1997년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [조선왕릉 가을 숲길] 인현왕후의 눈물이 서린 곳, 서오릉
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널고양의 서오릉은 서쪽에 5기의 능(경릉, 창릉, 익릉, 홍릉, 명릉)이 있다하여 이름 붙여졌습니다. 두번째로 규모가 큰 조선왕실의 왕릉군으로 모두 둘러보려면 2~3시간은 족히 걸릴만큼 묘역이 매우 큰데요. '신림(神林)'이라 불릴 만큼 자연경관이 잘 보존되어 있는 울창한 왕릉의 숲길을 걸어보세요. ※ 고양 서오릉 (사적 제198호) / 조선왕릉 (2009년 유네스코 세계문화유산)

programme.title: [신비롭고 아름다운 비경] 청송 주산지 EP.4
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널주산지는 조선 경종(1720년) 10월에 준공하였습니다. 주산지의 맑은 물은 주산현 꼭대기 별바위에서 계곡을 따라 흘러 주산지에 머무르고 주왕산 영봉에서 뻗친 울창한 수림으로 둘러싸여 있으며, 물위에 떠있는 듯한 왕버들과 어우러져 별천지에 온 것 같이 한적하면서도 아늑한 분위기를 자아냅니다. ※ 청송 주산지 일원 (명승 제 105호) / 청송세계지질공원 (2017년 유네스코 세계지질공원)

programme.title: Astrud Gilberto & Dizzy Gillespie
programme.sub-title: Gilberto, Gillespie & Skymasters - North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1982, Dutch big band The Skymasters accompanied monumental jazz trumpet legend Dizzy Gillespie and the Brazilian bossa nova singer Astrud Gilberto at the North Sea Jazz Festival in The Hague.

programme.title: Philip Catherine, Jean-Louis Rassinfosse & Chet Baker
programme.sub-title: Jazz a la Grand Place Chet Baker Trio
programme.desc: Two top-tier Belgian musicians – guitarist Philip Catherine and bassist Jean-Louis Rassinfosse – accompany American jazz trumpeter and vocalist Chet Baker during this 1985 performance at the beautiful Brussels Jazz Club, located on the Grand-Place, the Belgian capital's central square. The trio plays Charlie Mariano's “Crystal Bells”, the title track of their acclaimed 1983 album. Other songs played during this legendary concert include “Down” and “How Deep is the Ocean”.

programme.title: John Coltrane
programme.sub-title: I want to talk about you
programme.desc: Explore the music of one of the most influential and innovative saxophonists in jazz history: John Coltrane! Immerse yourself in this collection of remarkable performances from the early 1960s that showcase Coltrane's unparalleled artistry and unique sound during a transformative period in the artist's career. Recorded in various European cities, Coltrane is seen playing the songs “Autumn Leaves”, “Hackensack”, “My Favorite Things”, “I Want To Talk About You”, “Vigil”, and “Naima”. Tune in and experience why the music of John Coltrane has touched the lives of so many!

programme.title: Thelonious Monk
programme.desc: An extraordinary collection of clips in all jazz genres from the most beautiful concerts and the most special festivals, performed by the finest jazz musicians.

programme.title: Freddie Hubbard, Al Grey, Alvin Batiste & Al Casey
programme.sub-title: Freddie Hubbard & The Satchmo Legacy Live in 1987
programme.desc: Since 1977, Estival is a summer jazz festival in Switzerland, Lugano. Estival offers a thrilling and particularly surprising line-up that explores the rich world of contemporary music whilst promoting the understanding of different cultures, tolerance, and co-existence. This concert of Freddie Hubbard and the Satchmo Legacy in 1987, highlights the bebop legend's classic style and silky tone. Hubbard is an American jazz trumpeter whose unmistakable and influential tone contributed to new perspectives for modern jazz and bebop. He was also a well-known part of Art Blakey and the Jazz Messengers and is primarily known for playing bebop, hard bop, and post-bop styles from the early '60s onwards.

programme.title: Ahmad Jamal Trio
programme.sub-title: Ahmad Jamal Trio - North Sea Jazz
programme.desc: The North Sea Jazz Festival is the largest indoor music festival in the world, known globally as the event where the past, present and future of jazz are featured within three days. Next to a firm base of jazz as the festival's staple music genre, many others, such as blues, soul, funk, or hip hop, pass by. In 1989, legendary jazz pianist Ahmad Jamal brought his trio to the North Sea Jazz Festival. Accompanied by James Cammack on bass and David Bowler on drums, Jamal showcased his excellence.

programme.title: Charles Lloyd

programme.title: Louis Armstrong
programme.desc: Following a highly successful small-group jazz concert at New York Town Hall on May 17, 1947, Armstrong's manager Joe Glaser dissolved the Armstrong big band on August 13, 1947 and established a six-piece small group. This group was called the All Stars, and in 1964 Louis Armstrong recorded his biggest-selling record, Hello, Dolly! He made assorted television appearances, especially in the 1950s and 1960s – the recorded film was a TV Show in Australia when Armstrong was at the peak of his career. Armstrong kept up his busy tour schedule until a few years before his death in 1971. He also toured Africa, Europe, and Asia under sponsorship of the US State Department with great success, earning the nickname ‘Ambassador Satch'.

programme.sub-title: Martha Argerich – A Birthday Celebration III
programme.desc: On the occasion of her 80th birthday, Argentinian pianist Martha Argerich explored chamber music repertoire in this wonderful concert, recorded at Château de Chantilly, France. The ‘Grande Dame' of the piano is joined by various renowned artists, including pianists Lily Maisky and Iddo Bar-Shaï, violinists Tedi Papavrami and Akiko Suwanai, her daughter Lyda Chen-Argerich on viola, and cellist Mischa Maisky. On the program are Felix Mendelssohn's Piano Trio No. 1 in D minor, Op. 49 Leoš Janáček's Violin Sonata Franz Schubert's Rondo in A major, D. 951 and Johannes Brahms's Piano Quartet No. 3 in C minor, Op. 60. These performances were recorded on May 4 and June 13, 2021.

programme.title: Zhu Xiao-Mei
programme.desc: Chinese pianist Zhu Xiao-Mei performs J. S. Bach's Goldberg Variations (BWV 988) at the Leipzig Bach Festival. This June 2014 concert was recorded at St. Thomas Church, where Bach spent most time of his career as 'Thomaskantor', the musical director of the Thomanerchor church choir. The Goldberg Variations consist of one aria and a set of 30 variations. The work was first published in 1741 and was named after harpsichordist Johann Gottlieb Goldberg. In contrast to melodic variations on a theme, the Goldberg Variations do not follow the melody, but rather use the aria's bass line and chord progression. Every third variation in the series of 30 is a canon that follows an ascending pattern. The Goldberg Variations are among Bach's most celebrated works, which gained an even larger audience thanks to Glenn Gould's legendary recordings of the work in 1955 and 1981.

programme.title: Glass Marcano, Orchestre Symphonique Région Centre-Val de Loire/Tours & Stéphanie-Marie Degand
programme.sub-title: Beethoven Violin Concerto & Bizet Symphony in C
programme.desc: Young Venezuelan conductor Glass Marcano is a rising star. Having played in various local youth and symphony orchestras as a violinist, her first experience conducting an ensemble followed in 2012. In September 2020, she won the Orchestra Prize at La Maestra Competition – the first orchestra direction contest for women – held in Paris. In this concert, recorded at Opéra de Tours in February 2021, Marcano leads the Orchestre Symphonique Région Centre-Val de Loire/Tours in performances of two Romantic masterpieces. The program opens with Ludwig van Beethoven's Violin Concerto in D major, Op. 61, featuring Stéphanie-Marie Degand as the soloist. This piece is one of the most important works in its genre. The program concludes with Georges Bizet's 1855 Symphony in C major, written when the composer was only 17 years old.

programme.title: David Grimal & Les Dissonances
programme.sub-title: Beethoven - Symphony No. 4 in B-flat major, Op. 60
programme.desc: Les Dissonances is a collective of artists founded by violinist David Grimal in 2004. The conductorless ensemble consists of musicians from the most prestigious European orchestras, international soloists, and young talents. In this performance, Les Dissonances perform Ludwig van Beethoven's Symphony No. 4 in B-flat major, Op. 60. Count Franz von Oppersdorff, who adored Beethoven's Symphony No. 2, offered the composer a large sum to write a similar work. Completed in the autumn of 1806, the symphony's first performance was at a private concert in Vienna in March of 1807. Symphony No. 4 is often overshadowed by its revolutionary predecessor and successor. With its lightweight and cheerful nature, Symphony No. 4 contrasts with the two aforementioned works. This performance was recorded at Opéra de Dijon, France, in 2013.

Unfortunately there are not that vibrant anymore today. Coral reefs have suffered from the rise of water temperature, rise in acidity, destructive fishing methods and severe storms caused by climate change." - Peter Schneider. "Rainbow Reef Relaxation" is a 3-hour long, sweeping yet majestic & vibrant underwater journey to the world's most beautiful lagoons, as captured by Nature Relaxation collaborator Peter Schneider (Underwatercam) paired with ambient underwater sounds and brand new ambient music by the Cynic Project.
